        <p data-uuid="12029a8d811a4daa9dbb91ee547f9146"><b><dfn title="Stanford, Leland">Leland
            Stanford</dfn></b> was another important business leader of the
            late 1800s. He made a fortune selling equipment to miners. While governor of
            California, he became one of the founders of the state’s Central Pacific
            Railroad. He also founded Stanford University. Late in life, Stanford argued
            that industries should be owned and managed cooperatively by workers. He
            believed this would be the fulfillment of democracy.<br />
        </p>
